snippet.textDisplay:
$62 a core. So $4K for the processor. Lets say you spend another $2K on the rest of the system. Thats still $3K less than a Macintosh IIfx cost without adjusting for inflation. Inflation adjusted the iifx cost $17K...for the base model. "Macs are always over priced" you say. The Sun SPARC Station 2 started at $22K (not inflation adjusted) and went up from there. A Sony NeWS 3710 cost $16K. A Dell Station 425E cost $9287, roughly $300 more than a IIfx. A "discount" Northgate 486 system with color (remember, monochrome computers were still a thing) was $5200.


We have gotten spoiled with cheap computers. A Commodore 64 cost $595 at introduction and was a bargain. Thats $1576 in today dollars and didnt include a monitor or any storage. $1500 gets you a sweet gaming system with a 1440p monitor. Oh and all of those older computers would get smoked by a $55 Raspberry Pi4. $4K for a processor that would have been $500m and classified as a weapon in 1990? Yeah, thats cheap.
